call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Hartenstein (LAC) throws the ball out of bounds.
Horton-Tucker (LAL) makes incidental high-five contact with Mann (LAC) after Mann's shot attempt near the rim.
Mann (LAC) makes contact with James' (LAL) elbow during his shot attempt at the rim.  The contact is more than marginal and affects his shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) grabs Coffey (LAC) and affects his shot attempt at the rim.
Kennard (LAC) moves into Reaves' (LAL) path and initiates contact that drives him off of his spot and dislodges him from his screening position.
Westbrook (LAL) and Morris Sr. (LAC) mutually engage and disengage in the post.
Westbrook (LAL) steps forward into Morris Sr.'s (LAC) path and initiates foot to foot contact that affects his SQBR.
Westbrook (LAL) and Morris Sr. (LAC) make incidental foot to foot contact after Morris Sr. returns to the floor.
Horton-Tucker (LAL) initiates marginal contact with Mann (LAC) as the two players come together during the rebounding opportunity.
Covington (LAC) places his forearm against Westbrook's (LAL) body during the shot attempt and the contact is marginal.

Replay review of the out-of-bounds call on Covington (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Prior to Covington making contact with the ball, James (LAL) lands out of bounds with the ball in his possession.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Clippers.

Replay review of the foul called on Horton-Tucker (LAL) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful.  Horton-Tucker makes marginal contact with Jackson (LAC) in the backcourt that does not affect his SQBR.
Jackson (LAC) does not bring the ball from the backcourt into the frontcourt within the eight-second timeframe.
Mann (LAC) briefly holds Reaves (LAL) during the screen attempt and the contact is marginal.
Reaves (LAL) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
Jackson (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
